Lookey here man...you want some old school Korean BBQ style eats?  Then call ahead, make a reservation and don't eat all day.  This place is 500 square feet of all you can eat delicious Korean food straight out of Songton City, I swear.  It is by far the best all you can eat joint on the island with the kimchi dishes to go with it.  It is truly a hole in the wall joint that is in an alley with a line of people to get in.  It is small with like only 8 or 10 tables and COVID makes it even smaller.  But, this place smacks of flavor and don't forget to BYOB your booze as they don't sell it. This is no frills, down home Korean BBQ which you cook yourself and a must place to visit while in Honolulu.
